280
00:18:41,027 --> 00:18:43,747
and you're not scared of seeing them.

281
00:18:43,747 --> 00:18:47,497
They hit poverty overnight because of you,

282
00:18:47,497 --> 00:18:51,227
and your don't feel guilt in your conscience?

283
00:18:51,977 --> 00:18:56,096
You're talking about conscience and guilt?

284
00:18:56,096 --> 00:18:57,156
Fine.

285
00:18:57,156 --> 00:18:59,297
What does your conscience want?

286
00:18:59,297 --> 00:19:02,487
You failed at getting transaction records,

287
00:19:02,487 --> 00:19:06,157
and you haven't told Seonhui anything.

288
00:19:06,156 --> 00:19:09,026
That means you want something from me.

289
00:19:09,027 --> 00:19:11,747
I've  never asked you for much.

290
00:19:11,747 --> 00:19:13,567
Just one thing, that's all.

291
00:19:19,936 --> 00:19:23,546
This is the bond from the loan sharks.

292
00:19:24,336 --> 00:19:28,777
After this, I owe you nothing.

293
00:19:49,916 --> 00:19:51,636
He didn't set this up

294
00:19:51,636 --> 00:19:55,146
with the loan shark people, did he?

295
00:19:55,696 --> 00:19:58,756
Wait, he stole a family's fortune,

296
00:19:58,757 --> 00:20:01,807
and this is all he's going to offer me?

297
00:20:02,527 --> 00:20:04,927
Taesu's become very petty.

298
00:20:04,926 --> 00:20:06,196
Man...

299
00:20:15,287 --> 00:20:18,326
Only the management level and above

300
00:20:18,326 --> 00:20:20,116
in Security knew about it.

301
00:20:20,116 --> 00:20:23,057
That's over 20 people.

302
00:20:23,707 --> 00:20:26,347
This man was appointed relatively recently.

303
00:20:26,797 --> 00:20:29,427
Mr. Im Hanseok. Do you know him?

304
00:20:29,426 --> 00:20:31,576
No, I've never seen that name before.

305
00:20:33,047 --> 00:20:34,227
You're right.

306
00:20:34,227 --> 00:20:37,627
It happened after he was appointed.

307
00:20:37,626 --> 00:20:39,636
And only his contact number's missing.

308
00:20:40,146 --> 00:20:41,486
I'll check with the secretary's office.

309
00:20:44,326 --> 00:20:45,836
Hello, Mr. Choi.

310
00:20:45,836 --> 00:20:47,686
This is Jang Hyeondo.

311
00:20:47,686 --> 00:20:49,516
The executive secretary,

312
00:20:49,517 --> 00:20:52,376
the one who was just appointed.

313
00:20:52,376 --> 00:20:54,896
Can I get his personal number?

314
00:20:57,686 --> 00:20:59,006
What?

315
00:21:00,237 --> 00:21:03,187
You don't have his number?

316
00:21:05,967 --> 00:21:07,387
Okay.

317
00:21:18,487 --> 00:21:19,826
Isn't it simpler to hand her over

318
00:21:19,826 --> 00:21:23,186
to the loan sharks than to pay her debt off?

319
00:21:24,487 --> 00:21:26,747
Even to you,

320
00:21:26,747 --> 00:21:30,366
she didn't look like she'd go away quietly?

321
00:21:31,406 --> 00:21:34,506
Why don't you hand her over?

322
00:21:34,507 --> 00:21:36,797
If I call them right now...

323
00:21:37,336 --> 00:21:39,606
The thing about people is that

324
00:21:39,606 --> 00:21:44,007
they need hope or desire to be cautious.

325
00:21:44,007 --> 00:21:46,047
Women like Lee Jeongae become

326
00:21:46,047 --> 00:21:49,606
unpredictable if they are pushed too far.

327
00:21:49,606 --> 00:21:51,976
If things go wrong after I hand her over to

328
00:21:51,977 --> 00:21:55,157
the loan sharks, she'll come after me.

329
00:21:58,547 --> 00:22:01,957
There's one thing I'm worried about.

330
00:22:04,287 --> 00:22:09,777
Why did she need to take out a loan?

331
00:22:12,057 --> 00:22:13,636
Should I find out?

332
00:22:14,436 --> 00:22:15,776
Yes.

333
00:22:16,156 --> 00:22:18,716
She loved spending money, but she wasn't

334
00:22:18,717 --> 00:22:22,637
reckless enough to turn to loan sharks.

335
00:22:46,836 --> 00:22:49,807
Kids, mommy's here.

336
00:22:49,807 --> 00:22:51,807
Hello.

337
00:22:51,807 --> 00:22:52,846
Hi.

338
00:22:52,846 --> 00:22:54,517
These are for you.

339
00:22:54,517 --> 00:22:55,937
Thank you.

340
00:22:55,936 --> 00:22:58,726
- Thank you. / - Sure.

341
00:22:59,406 --> 00:23:01,906
What brings you here?

342
00:23:01,906 --> 00:23:04,236
I came to see you, mom.

343
00:23:04,237 --> 00:23:06,846
Eunha is inside.

344
00:23:06,846 --> 00:23:08,487
Okay.

345
00:23:08,487 --> 00:23:12,467
You said you're broke, so stop bringing snacks.

346
00:23:12,467 --> 00:23:15,367
I might be getting some money soon.

347
00:23:15,366 --> 00:23:18,336
This is why people should have lots of kids.

348
00:23:18,336 --> 00:23:21,426
What are you talking about?

349
00:23:21,426 --> 00:23:22,706
It's nothing.

350
00:23:22,707 --> 00:23:25,297
You have lots of kids, so you should see.

351
00:23:25,297 --> 00:23:27,886
One of them might take care of you.

352
00:23:27,886 --> 00:23:30,126
Unlike other mugs, I'm trying to

353
00:23:30,126 --> 00:23:34,116
make the top part of the handle round.

354
00:23:34,116 --> 00:23:37,226
And I want to put a flower motif on it.

355
00:23:37,227 --> 00:23:38,177
Using graphics.

356
00:23:38,176 --> 00:23:39,596
Is that possible?

357
00:23:46,146 --> 00:23:48,317
Ma'am!

358
00:23:48,317 --> 00:23:49,757
Yes?

359
00:23:52,457 --> 00:23:55,157
Did you remove the invitations from here?

360
00:23:55,156 --> 00:23:56,516
No.

361
00:23:57,376 --> 00:23:59,836
Did I put them somewhere else?

362
00:23:59,836 --> 00:24:00,606
What is it?

363
00:24:00,606 --> 00:24:03,206
Do you need an invitation to get in?

364
00:24:03,207 --> 00:24:04,747
No,

365
00:24:04,747 --> 00:24:08,616
my face is all I need. I don't need one.

366
00:24:10,007 --> 00:24:11,397
Let's go.

367
00:24:19,267 --> 00:24:21,897
Okay. Take care of it,

368
00:24:21,896 --> 00:24:24,067
and I'll talk to you on Monday.

369
00:24:25,037 --> 00:24:28,717
I can't let Kim Jiwan stay at my company.

370
00:24:31,307 --> 00:24:36,287
He's working at a place like this?

371
00:24:39,336 --> 00:24:40,757
Oh, no!

372
00:24:41,487 --> 00:24:43,927
He's the one who stole my invitations?

373
00:24:43,926 --> 00:24:45,226
Okay. Bye.

374
00:24:46,866 --> 00:24:49,486
Honey, if you're done, let's go and eat.

375
00:24:49,487 --> 00:24:50,247
Honey!

376
00:24:50,247 --> 00:24:52,517
I want to buy this painting!

377
00:24:56,057 --> 00:24:57,447
This one?

378
00:24:57,446 --> 00:25:01,616
The colors and the divided composition would

379
00:25:01,616 --> 00:25:04,386
- look great in our living room... / - Whatever.

380
00:25:04,386 --> 00:25:06,106
How much is it?

381
00:25:06,106 --> 00:25:08,696
How many times must I tell you it's vulgar to

382
00:25:08,696 --> 00:25:11,286
talk of price when it comes to masterpieces?

383
00:25:11,287 --> 00:25:12,156
So you're saying

384
00:25:12,156 --> 00:25:16,336
if I heard the price, I'd have a heart attack?

385
00:25:16,336 --> 00:25:18,576
If you're not going to buy it, let's leave.

386
00:25:18,576 --> 00:25:21,336
Thank you for letting me escape from here.

387
00:25:28,336 --> 00:25:31,416
The food here is good. Let's come here often.

388
00:25:31,416 --> 00:25:35,586
I only get invitations from nice places.

389
00:25:36,567 --> 00:25:39,356
- He stole the invitation for here? / - What?

390
00:25:39,356 --> 00:25:40,856
What did you say?

391
00:25:40,856 --> 00:25:44,896
It's nothing. Keep eating, Mr. Jang Taesu.

392
00:25:45,507 --> 00:25:49,147
There are no tables by the window?

393
00:25:49,686 --> 00:25:50,966
What's that?

394
00:25:50,967 --> 00:25:52,307
Isn't that Hyeondo's voice?

395
00:25:52,307 --> 00:25:54,366
No, that isn't Hyeondo's voice.

396
00:25:54,366 --> 00:25:56,007
You must be going deaf.

397
00:25:56,007 --> 00:25:57,237
Have some more wine.

398
00:25:57,237 --> 00:25:58,667
Here.

399
00:26:03,317 --> 00:26:04,686
Go inside...

400
00:26:11,227 --> 00:26:12,836
What are you doing?

401
00:26:14,906 --> 00:26:17,076
I can't cut the steak.

402
00:26:17,076 --> 00:26:19,517
Can you cut it for me?

403
00:26:19,517 --> 00:26:23,836
Still, don't throw your steak at my plate.

404
00:26:23,836 --> 00:26:26,067
Okay. Let's go.

405
00:26:40,836 --> 00:26:42,346
Have lunch before you leave.

406
00:26:42,346 --> 00:26:45,656
I have to leave, too, so clean up afterwards.

407
00:26:45,656 --> 00:26:48,686
I'm not eating. You eat.

408
00:26:48,686 --> 00:26:50,276
Fine. Just starve yourself.

409
00:26:50,277 --> 00:26:52,317
It's your stomach, not mine.

410
00:26:56,436 --> 00:26:59,016
They said it's now or never,

411
00:26:59,017 --> 00:27:02,567
so I wanted to ask if I should review anything.

412
00:27:02,567 --> 00:27:04,947
I was going to talk to you about Ohyeah Media.

413
00:27:04,946 --> 00:27:06,076
I don't think that place is legit.

414
00:27:06,076 --> 00:27:07,247
Something seems wrong.

415
00:27:07,247 --> 00:27:08,717
What do you mean?

416
00:27:08,717 --> 00:27:11,617
They steal up-and-coming writers' ideas.

417
00:27:11,616 --> 00:27:13,106
I heard they turn you into their slave.

418
00:27:13,106 --> 00:27:14,936
Anyway, their reputation isn't good.

419
00:27:14,936 --> 00:27:16,326
If you sign a contract with them,

420
00:27:16,326 --> 00:27:19,267
you might end up being in planning forever.

421
00:27:19,267 --> 00:27:21,267
At least they'll pay me signing bonus.

422
00:27:21,267 --> 00:27:23,947
They will, but it'll be pennies.

423
00:27:23,946 --> 00:27:25,506
Anyway, read the contract carefully

424
00:27:25,507 --> 00:27:27,366
and bring it to me. I'll ask around.

425
00:27:27,366 --> 00:27:29,997
Director, we're ready.

426
00:27:29,997 --> 00:27:31,307
Just a second.

427
00:27:31,307 --> 00:27:33,886
Ms. Kang, the shooting's about to start,

428
00:27:33,886 --> 00:27:37,496
so don't sign anything just yet, okay?

429
00:27:39,317 --> 00:27:41,596
But what if,

430
00:27:41,596 --> 00:27:43,537
like the guy said,

431
00:27:43,537 --> 00:27:46,717
this is the best opportunity for me?

432
00:27:46,717 --> 00:27:49,407
You might end up in some serious trouble.

433
00:27:49,406 --> 00:27:50,656
But it could work out.

434
00:27:50,656 --> 00:27:52,807
It could work out really well.

435
00:27:52,807 --> 00:27:54,616
If I can get the money...

436
00:27:54,616 --> 00:27:56,196
Are you doing this for money?

437
00:27:56,196 --> 00:27:58,266
Then, you'll definitely end up big trouble!

438
00:27:58,267 --> 00:28:02,096
They can sniff out writers in need of money!

439
00:28:02,096 --> 00:28:03,987
They'll suck you dry!

440
00:28:03,987 --> 00:28:05,557
No, Ms. Kang! Don't do it!

441
00:28:05,557 --> 00:28:06,707
I'm sorry.

442
00:28:06,707 --> 00:28:07,587
I have to go.

443
00:28:07,586 --> 00:28:08,956
Ms. Kang!

444
00:28:19,307 --> 00:28:22,086
You're going to read every line?

445
00:28:22,086 --> 00:28:24,186
This society is based on trust.

446
00:28:24,186 --> 00:28:26,236
Do you see $100,000 there?

447
00:28:26,237 --> 00:28:29,836
You'll get it when the contract is finalized.

448
00:28:29,836 --> 00:28:32,616
I'm a man of my words.

449
00:28:33,436 --> 00:28:36,926
Sign there.

450
00:28:40,817 --> 00:28:44,156
They can sniff out writers in need of money!

451
00:28:44,156 --> 00:28:46,366
They'll suck you dry!

452
00:28:46,366 --> 00:28:48,966
No, Ms. Kang! Don't do it!

453
00:28:49,646 --> 00:28:51,706
When you're gone,

454
00:28:51,707 --> 00:28:54,597
several lower positions can be spared.

455
00:28:54,596 --> 00:28:56,646
Get a conscience!

456
00:29:02,326 --> 00:29:04,027
You're not going to sign it?

457
00:29:04,027 --> 00:29:05,487
What?

458
00:29:14,906 --> 00:29:16,226
If you don't want to, forget it.

459
00:29:16,227 --> 00:29:17,297
No!

460
00:29:17,297 --> 00:29:19,396
I'm signing it right now.

461
00:29:26,856 --> 00:29:28,226
Oh, my!

462
00:29:30,977 --> 00:29:32,867
What the heck are you doing?

463
00:29:32,866 --> 00:29:34,446
I'm her mom,

464
00:29:34,446 --> 00:29:36,756
so I'm going to do something here.

465
00:29:36,757 --> 00:29:37,487
Mom.

466
00:29:37,487 --> 00:29:38,447
Mom, what are you doing?

467
00:29:38,446 --> 00:29:40,326
You don't know anything, so just leave.

468
00:29:41,237 --> 00:29:42,856
I don't know anything? How do you know?

469
00:29:42,856 --> 00:29:45,787
I know more about contracts than you do.

470
00:29:45,787 --> 00:29:48,007
I worked at a bank for 10 years, you know?

471
00:29:48,007 --> 00:29:49,317
Let me see this.

472
00:29:52,376 --> 00:29:54,676
Signing bonus, $100,000.

473
00:30:02,777 --> 00:30:06,096
See? I knew it.

474
00:30:06,096 --> 00:30:07,896
It says $100,000,

475
00:30:07,896 --> 00:30:08,676
but what?

476
00:30:08,676 --> 00:30:11,366
The signing bonus is 10%?

477
00:30:11,366 --> 00:30:13,716
And the contract period is 10 years?

478
00:30:13,717 --> 00:30:17,707
Your drama must air within the first year to get the signing bonus?

479
00:30:17,707 --> 00:30:19,007
What?

480
00:30:20,146 --> 00:30:21,047
Hey!

481
00:30:21,047 --> 00:30:22,086
Who are you?

482
00:30:22,086 --> 00:30:24,727
How dare you try to con my daughter?

483
00:30:24,727 --> 00:30:26,817
You think my daughter's on idiot?

484
00:30:26,817 --> 00:30:28,406
Are you mad?

485
00:30:28,406 --> 00:30:30,567
You want me to call the police?

486
00:30:30,567 --> 00:30:32,057
We must call the police!

487
00:30:32,057 --> 00:30:35,376
I'll call them and tell them to arrest you!

488
00:30:35,376 --> 00:30:36,656
Mom, what are you doing? It's embarrassing!

489
00:30:36,656 --> 00:30:37,966
What the heck!

490
00:30:37,967 --> 00:30:38,947
How dare you!

491
00:30:38,946 --> 00:30:42,196
Let go! What are you doing to my mom!

492
00:30:43,257 --> 00:30:44,887
Why you little!

493
00:30:46,557 --> 00:30:48,477
Mom, nice! Good job, mom!

494
00:30:48,477 --> 00:30:51,357
How dare you call this a contract!

495
00:30:51,356 --> 00:30:53,896
Good job, mom.

496
00:30:54,507 --> 00:30:56,846
Such an idiot.

497
00:30:56,846 --> 00:30:59,376
You have no street smarts.

498
00:30:59,376 --> 00:31:01,507
Even if you're desperate,

499
00:31:01,507 --> 00:31:04,116
you should know what's good or bad.

500
00:31:05,166 --> 00:31:07,006
How did you know?

501
00:31:08,336 --> 00:31:12,297
That producer named Heo Seonggeun called.

502
00:31:12,906 --> 00:31:14,686
Oh, he conned you, but he couldn't stand

503
00:31:14,686 --> 00:31:18,876
watching you being conned by someone else.

504
00:31:21,307 --> 00:31:22,916
Don't laugh.

505
00:31:23,896 --> 00:31:26,557
You don't have to do this.

506
00:31:26,557 --> 00:31:28,527
If your dad found out what you did,

507
00:31:28,527 --> 00:31:31,287
he'll be even more miserable.

508
00:31:32,896 --> 00:31:34,466
Mom,

509
00:31:35,156 --> 00:31:37,626
I'm sorry about the other night.

510
00:31:37,626 --> 00:31:39,886
I'm hot. Get away from me.

511
00:31:41,767 --> 00:31:44,297
She never says anything nice.

512
00:31:51,707 --> 00:31:54,407
Don't act rashly for your dad's sake.

513
00:31:55,957 --> 00:31:59,777
I can't do anything for him anyway.

514
00:32:00,666 --> 00:32:02,966
You don't need to do anything.

515
00:32:02,967 --> 00:32:04,697
I'll take care of dad.

516
00:32:04,696 --> 00:32:06,946
When I get involved, things just work out.

517
00:32:06,946 --> 00:32:09,336
I raised an idiot like you into a decent woman,

518
00:32:09,336 --> 00:32:10,936
so nothing's impossible for me.

519
00:32:14,057 --> 00:32:16,346
I'm Oh Minja.

520
00:32:33,477 --> 00:32:34,477
What's this?

521
00:32:34,477 --> 00:32:36,647
Is it a gift or a bribe?

522
00:32:37,576 --> 00:32:39,307
Gift or bribe, I'm not the least interested

523
00:32:39,307 --> 00:32:41,866
in giving anything to you, mom,

524
00:32:41,866 --> 00:32:44,226
but Eunsu is so nice.

525
00:32:44,227 --> 00:32:47,037
She made this with her pretty hands

526
00:32:47,037 --> 00:32:48,727
to give to you!

527
00:32:54,166 --> 00:32:56,886
Why did I ever give birth to him?

528
00:32:57,207 --> 00:32:59,977
I should tell Hyeongyu to come home soon!

529
00:33:16,787 --> 00:33:19,507
This mug is one of a kind.

530
00:33:19,507 --> 00:33:23,747
This design was inspired by you.

531
00:33:25,807 --> 00:33:28,426
Not bad.

532
00:33:40,277 --> 00:33:41,537
- What? / - Huh?

533
00:33:42,047 --> 00:33:43,787
Have you gone deaf?

534
00:33:43,787 --> 00:33:45,106
I'm old.

535
00:33:45,106 --> 00:33:46,916
I can't be bothered.

536
00:33:46,916 --> 00:33:49,336
So go ahead and date. I don't care.

537
00:33:51,866 --> 00:33:53,616
- Do you mean it? / - Really?

538
00:33:54,856 --> 00:33:57,406
Why do you keep asking me that?

539
00:33:57,406 --> 00:33:59,146
You want me to take it back?

540
00:34:00,047 --> 00:34:01,396
No...

541
00:34:01,396 --> 00:34:02,277
No, mom!

542
00:34:02,277 --> 00:34:04,096
We're just so happy, that's why, mom.

543
00:34:04,096 --> 00:34:05,527
Don't be so happy.

544
00:34:05,527 --> 00:34:07,557
My "Yes" means very little.

545
00:34:07,557 --> 00:34:09,246
Mom...

546
00:34:09,246 --> 00:34:10,716
Thank you.

547
00:34:10,717 --> 00:34:12,527
But that's all.

548
00:34:12,527 --> 00:34:15,336
Trying to break you up is a waste of energy.

549
00:34:15,336 --> 00:34:16,697
That was hard on me, too.

550
00:34:16,697 --> 00:34:18,527
I don't enjoy playing the bad guy, you know?

551
00:34:18,527 --> 00:34:19,436
So keep dating.

552
00:34:19,436 --> 00:34:21,586
Date as much as you want and break up.

553
00:34:21,586 --> 00:34:24,146
But you handle your father. I can't.

554
00:34:24,146 --> 00:34:25,786
You can't ask me that.

555
00:34:25,786 --> 00:34:28,726
